content: Hi. This failure https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/81172#issuecomment-779442186 looks unrelated to the PR. Is a retry appropriate?

@Simon Sapin That PR adds feature(intra_doc_pointers) in two places, and changes src/test/rustdoc/intra-doc/libstd-re-export.rs. Maybe that indirectly triggered the problem?
I suppose you can just retry and see if the same thing happens.
Though, i see no way in which rustdoc will create a page with two elements with id="rustdoc-vars"
this sounds like there's a rustdoc bug somewhere
